Reasoning: 
- cs.RO (Robotics) is the most likely category as the paper deals with multi-robot path planning and includes hardware experiments on non-holonomic robots. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is also likely as the paper proposes an algorithmic framework for solving a complex planning problem. 
- cs.SY (Systems and Control) is relevant as the paper deals with controlling multiple robots to achieve a common goal. 
- cs.MA (Multi-Agent Systems) is relevant as the paper deals with multiple agents (robots) interacting with each other. 
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is relevant as the paper proposes a new algorithmic framework for solving a planning problem.
